[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Everyone is getting Google Omni wrong. People are comparing Omni to Seedance 2 by making fight videos and saying, "Look, Omni sucks." But honestly, I think most people are missing the point. Omni is not trying to be Seedance 2. Omni is not the best text-to-video or'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image-to-video model that there is. But, it is the best video-to-video model, and that matters a lot. Now, we can think of this breakthrough as Omni being the nano banana moment for video.'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It is not just about generating a clip from scratch. It is about editing, transforming, remixing, and controlling video through natural language, and that is a completely different thing, especially for one huge situation.'

[00:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Because if you\'re a real filmmaker, creator, editor, or visual storyteller, what you need is the ability to apply AI to real footage, and that\'s what we can do. For example, I can instantly change'

[00:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the lighting in my shot while still making it look completely believable. Means I can enhance my studio, and also add interesting special effects while keeping the authenticity of my real performance for you here. The future of'

[01:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI is not replacing standard creative tools. It\'s working collaboratively with them. I\'m going to show you the possibilities of taking real footage and changing the environment, the lighting, and visual effects, transforming the'

[01:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'environment, and creating complex text animations on top of your videos. Google Omni can respond to audio input and turn a basic clip into something much more cinematic, useful, or even'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'strange. And this is really where Omni becomes very interesting. Google describes Gemini Omni Flash as a model that can create from any input, and it\'s being rolled out into Gemini,'

